translate ru SarahAndNick1_4d00770b:
    # "Sarah woke to the earliest beams of light from the dawn."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_692394c5:
    # "Sheltered, warmed by the fire and waking to the gentle and ethereal light of the Hyral mountains splintering on the fog, Sarah imagined herself dreaming."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_36af9079:
    # "The light seemed to diffuse, turning beams into almost a mist of sun."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_4172792e:
    # "Perhaps she had died, she thought, and for her troubled life the gods had seen fit to reward her."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d9f6a02e:
    # "But as she drew in the could mountain air, she was reminded that she was still on the mortal plan."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_5ac21ff2:
    # "Opposite of her, she could see Nick was still sleeping. The rising and falling of his chest telling her he had, thankfully, not died in his sleep during the night."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_a04d1d1c:
    # "As she put her hands against the cave floor, she felt the cold stones press against her palms."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_1c8bcd1e:
    # "It was a strange kind of coldness, the kind that only existed in places that never knew anything other than cold."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e04ba479:
    # "Outside, the landscape was still covered in snow."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_7e03a1c3:
    # "What little Sarah knew of this place, she knew that the snow here was permanent. No passing of the seasons affected it."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_bb22c62c:
    # "As she looked towards Nick and herself, and made an account of what little they had, she began to worry."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_a601f4c4:
    # "Their clothes were a poor fit for the cold."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_15898af5:
    # "The cave and the campfire went a long way in keeping them warm, but they had no food. They couldn't stay in the cave for long or they would starve."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_01e2f4f3:
    # "They would have to set out soon."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b50e33d8:
    # "But the nearest human settlement was hundreds of miles by coast."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_3d441fb1:
    # "Worse still, they could not follow the coastline. The jagged rocks and stabbing mountains that rose up towards the heavens made a natural barrier against the ocean."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_1c8b5276:
    # "This small bay was a rare exception in an otherwise inhospitable land."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_ab87ae51:
    # "Sarah tried to conceive of a plan."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_f1880cb6:
    # "They would have to travel inwards, up through the Hyral mountains. A tough journey, even when prepared. And they were not prepared."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b576f3b7:
    # "An easy mistake and they would starve or freeze to death. Possibly both."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_54c3308b:
    # "All this was enough to trouble Sarah, had she not also known what the Hyral mountains were most famous for."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_cb658c9e:
    # "The homeland of the orcs and goblins."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_a76b80f5:
    # "Once a formidable race that had ruled over large swathes of land, over time they had been driven back by the advance of human civilization."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c4c596a8:
    # "The orcs made impressive warriors, but they did not have the organization to field large armies the way humans did."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_0adb40bf:
    # "Their smaller warbands were excellent for raiding, but against the armies of humanity, and especially the Mythran empire, they stood no chance."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b5da493b:
    # "The orcs were pushed back until eventually only their ancestral homeland remained. The Hyral mountains."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b17cbfb9:
    # "These mountains, dangerous and inhospitable, could not support large armies in the way the open plains could."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_86c2790e:
    # "In this place, the orcs could play to their advantages."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_68c8b90c:
    # "But rather than settle the fight, humanity had simply considered it finished."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_96dcaaba:
    # "The orcs were a small threat, worth little more than the occasional consideration."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d2a5b43a:
    # "Let them have the mountains."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_928bb9b6:
    # "And so the orcs, forgotten and ignored, did what all irrelevant peoples did. They obsessed over the trivial and small things of life."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e2057349:
    # "They fought among each other. They carried out the occasional raid when they dared."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_ba1f4e1f:
    # "Where once they had ruled empires, now they squabbled over who might hold claim over a pretty farm girl that was captured in some insignificant raid on a frontier town."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_4e08301d:
    # "Meanwhile, the Mythran empire was not in a mood to waste its legions to rescue poor farmers."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_8927f8b5:
    # "This was the peace that had settled on the lands between humans and orcs."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_49a2449e:
    # "A brutal peace, where as often, the weakest and poorest were made to pay the price."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c2d2bb53:
    # "Sarah shuddered as she put all of the threats together."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_5ce8bd46:
    # "She had no illusions what would happen if she fell into the hands of an orc warband."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_eebaa0d7:
    # "She sighed, how had she allowed herself to fall into this situation."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_6e3f49f8:
    # "Looking across the cave, she saw Nick, still sleeping."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_25662f1a:
    # "That was it. Her one ally. Her one resource."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_10b8d3fc:
    # "He could work a ship and looked strong enough, but would he be strong enough to fight off an orc attack?."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c349ae56:
    # "Slowly, she saw him begin to stir."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c7fa5a4e:
    # nick "Hey."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d050a518:
    # "His voice was soft. Likely still weakened by the frigid water."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_2143beba:
    # s "Hey. Did you get any good sleep?"
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_a0b2bcce:
    # "He slightly nodded."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_115938de:
    # nick "I think I did."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_3998b279:
    # "She saw him look outside of the cave."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_50da4c35:
    # nick "We're so screwed..."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_cdb852db:
    # s "Don't say that. We'll need to keep our hopes of if we want any chance of getting out of here."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_8e80e717:
    # "He looked back at her."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_0a1cc442:
    # nick "Getting out of here? We're in the middle of the Hyral mountains. Better if we'd have just drowned."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_2d961aa5:
    # "Sarah grew frustrated."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b00da9d6:
    # s "Well, if you want, go ahead and dive in then. I'm going to try and get out of here, alive."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_afc3219b:
    # "She saw him lower his head."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_55e7927b:
    # nick "Sorry, I just thought...our odds aren't exactly good."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_2c900fea:
    # s "Trust me, I know that."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e4ce48ff:
    # "Sarah spoke with Nick, going through their options."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b632ed65:
    # "In the end, each understood that no matter what, there was one reality they could not ignore."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_24a18b3d:
    # "There was no food here, so they could not stay. The longer they did, the worse their food situation would get."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_39745bb4:
    # s "Right, so we agree? We'll need to leave. Today."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e590eecb:
    # "Nick nodded."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_1fe5a4aa:
    # "She could see the fear on his face."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_beb01e8b:
    # "He might have had a tough life growing up, but deep down he was still a city boy, unfamiliar with these harsh lands."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_f1add58b:
    # "For a brief moment, Sarah thought that Belmont would have known what to do. He would have taken charge."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d74dbb3a:
    # "Sarah shook her head. She had made her choice, and now this was it."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d796ca21:
    # "She'd have to take the lead, even though she was no more prepared for it than Nick."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_ad02a7fa:
    # s "Let's get packing."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b778ee06:
    # "Together, they started working, packing what little they had. Fixing their clothes as best they could against the cold."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_a60f9da7:
    # "Before long, they were finished and stood near the entrance of the cave."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_205bb7a2:
    # "Looking out, Sarah saw the endless fields of snow before her. The looming mountains."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_0d032fa9:
    # "She was afraid."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c635ffe6:
    # "She knew she could not stay here, but she equally feared leaving the safety of the cave."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_33cac254:
    # "Despite all her fears, Sarah began her journey same as any other, with a single step."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_7cf5a507:
    # "Instantly, the cold advanced on them."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_bf0999a3:
    # "Sarah forced herself to keep to a steady march as she plowed through the thick layer of snow."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_58ca595f:
    # "It wasn't long before the cave was far behind them and the whole world seemed to be made out of snow."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_795b9546:
    # "There was so much of it, a pure white, that it at times disoriented her."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_625d59ce:
    # "With each passing step, the brutal winds of the Hyral Mountains grew harsher and harsher, as if warning them to turn back."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_dec6155a:
    # "This was not a land made for people."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_bfc58583:
    # "Only the brutish orcs could survive in a place so hostile to life."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_b3ecbe63:
    # "As the winds grew in intensity, they ripped and tore at both Sarah and Nick's cloak."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_24090a3c:
    # "Sarah let slip the garment, only for a moment, and a cold that cut deep into her skin rushed in."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c3d6e4ce:
    # "Growing in intensity by each passing moment, the wind began to howl."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_31737f9e:
    # "A shrieking sound bombarded their ears, as the hardened snow pelted at their faces like rocks."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_6df8b1d6:
    # "And the cold sank deeper and deeper through their fabrics, and skin, taking rest deep in their bones."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_8f2f6620:
    # "Step by step, Sarah kept pushing forward, because to stop was certain death."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_74e00f6a:
    # "Still, despite the best of her hopes, she began to fear for the worst."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c699dbee:
    # "Neither of them had much experience surviving out in the wild."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_f6acf1b1:
    # "And these mountains could prove a test for the most tested of veterans."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_f043ef6d:
    # "So for a moment, she wondered."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d981defe:
    # "What if she had made a mistake."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_ea46ea51:
    # "To leave the safety of the cave, to be exposed to the elements, or worse..."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e71a0464:
    # "Her own mortality was suddenly a very conscious fact."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e020e7b0:
    # "Sarah shook her head and forced herself to keep moving."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e16f8c85:
    # "No, horrible as this was, the cave meant accepting a slow death."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d6266150:
    # "Despite the torture of the howling blizzard, at least, they might live."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_4c1d530f:
    # "They pressed on, neither speaking, not until the torment becam too much and their exhaustion broke them."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_6458c35b:
    # nick "I can't feel my feet...my hands...my...anything..."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_42c5d845:
    # "His voice was soft, almost hard to hear over they gyre."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c14b2cc3:
    # s "Just a bit more."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_d9781af0:
    # s "I think...I see a spot up that hill where we can rest."
    s ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_54986b7d:
    # "Nick walked up beside her."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_f7d48fb5:
    # nick "Finally..."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_1bb0e2a1:
    # nick "Some rest...a fire..."
    nick ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_30a6abf9:
    # "Sarah frowned."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_ba7d2f74:
    # "The cold was overpowering. Her limbs trembled."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_85754b6e:
    # "She wanted nothing more than heat...but a fire was a risk."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_e5eb0db6:
    # "Out here, they would stand out in the dark. And who knew what lurked in the dark."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_8702de44:
    # "Then again, she doubted anyone but them would be crazy enough to endure this blizzard."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_0d438c7b:
    # "And she feared the cold almost as much as any creature or beast."
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_c0bb8c4b:
    # "What if they collapsed from exhaustion? Only to die in their sleep from the exposure to the cold?"
    ""

translate ru SarahAndNick1_81292677:
    # "Sarah wasn't sure what the best option was."
    ""

